<TITLE> DCC to host 360 Eid congregations </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 29 (bdnews24.com)The capital will see a total of 360 Eid-ul-Fitr congregations in the city's 90 wards this year, with the main congregation to be held at the National Eidgah premises. Hosted by Dhaka City Corporation, the main congregation will begin at 8:30am and be led by Khatib of the National Mosque, Mufti Mohammad Nooruddin. If weather becomes inclement, the location will be shifted to Baitul Mokarram National Mosque. Each of Dhaka's 90 wards will hold four congregations to make a total of 360 gatherings hosted by DCC. Most of these congregations will be locally scheduled, said a DCC statement Monday. Five congregations will be held by the Islamic Foundation at the Baitul Mokarram mosque. DCC has scheduled the congregations for 7:30am, 8:30am, 9:30am, 10:30am and the last at 11:15am. Two congregations will be held at the central mosque of Dhaka University, one at 8:00am and another at 9:00am. Two more will be held at 8:00am on the premises of DU's Salimullah Hall and the lawn of Shahidullah Hall. bdne
